comments.body:
Thanks for reaching out, @90degs2infty!

@TomSweeneyRedHat, I think we should drop mentioning `podman search` as the first command.  `search` is not a standardized endpoint on the registries, so users may have varying experiences and, as mentioned here, may not have the same configurations on their systems.  I suggest to use `podman pull` instead.

@90degs2infty, which distribution are you running?  All distros should ship with a least one `unqualified-search-registries` .
